# Typography System

## Font Metric Overrides

Suisse Intl has unusually large internal ascender/descender metrics. Without correction, this causes:
- Tall text cursors in inputs
- Inconsistent vertical rhythm
- Elements appearing taller than designed

The `@font-face` declarations in `_fonts.scss` include metric overrides:
- `ascent-override: 85%`
- `descent-override: 15%`
- `line-gap-override: 0%`

These values compress the font's vertical bounds to match design intent.

**Do not remove these overrides.** They are essential for proper rendering.

## Line-Height Tokens

Line-heights use unitless ratios that scale with font size:

| Token | Value | Use Case |
|-------|-------|----------|
| `--font-leading-none` | 1 | Buttons, inputs, single-line |
| `--font-leading-snug` | 1.33 | Headlines, code |
| `--font-leading-normal` | 1.43 | Body text |
| `--font-leading-relaxed` | 1.5 | Large body, labels |
| `--font-leading-loose` | 1.6 | Extra spacing |

The build script (`scripts/build-tokens.js`) outputs these as unitless values. The `font/leading` pattern is intentionally excluded from `needsPxUnits()`.

## Do Not

- Add `px` suffix to line-height tokens
- Remove font metric overrides from `_fonts.scss`
- Use hardcoded pixel line-heights in components
